review_blob: Pretty good barely wine. Its a little creamy which is good but also kinda weird. Im assuming its from the cognac. Very malty!

This is a great coffee porter. Id say its more of a stout than a porter but really there is no difference. The bitterness all comes from the coffee, not the hops because who the fuck wants a hoppy porter? No one. This beer is really well done and they should be proud and sell it more places.
Smells like a weird juice. This beer has layers just like an ogre. It keeps changing as it goes down your mouth. Its not that great but still interesting.
This tastes just like my mint stout! That said its delicious! Very minty and it actually has an aroma unlike a lot of beers.
The taste is great, very apply. But its dry and hits the mouth wrong. I probably wouldnt get this again.
